# Feature Completion Checklist (Mandatory)

**Authority:** `00_architecture_authority.mdc` Â· **Detail:** `doc/ARCHITECTURE_V2_AGENT_RULES.md` Â§ Architecture Compliance Checklist

A feature is **NOT complete** unless every **applicable** item below is satisfied.

## Mandatory checklist

```
â–ˇ API
   /api/v1 endpoint in modules/<domain>/routes/
   Registered in mountVersionedApi.ts
   Zod validation, sendSuccess/handleRouteError

â–ˇ Tenant Isolation
   tenant_id on all queries via TenantRepository
   req.tenantId only â€” never client-supplied tenant_id
   Socket events scoped to tenant:${tenantId}

â–ˇ Audit Trail
   withAudit() or recordDomainMutation() on mutations
   IP/user-agent via auditRequestContextMiddleware

â–ˇ Real-Time Synchronization
   emitEntityEvent() or emitFinancialPosted() after PostgreSQL commit
   Frontend: socket listener + React Query invalidateQueries / setQueryData
   No local-only updates for shared business entities

â–ˇ Permissions
   Permission in shared/rbac/permissions.ts
   npm run build:backend
   requirePermission() on routes
   usePermissions() on UI actions

â–ˇ Version Conflict Handling
   checkEntityLwwConflict() where entity has version column
   HTTP 409 CONFLICT with { serverVersion }
   UI informs user on conflict

â–ˇ Reporting Integration
   (If financial or report-facing)
   Calculations in shared/financial-core/ or shared/report-engines/
   Report service imports reportEngines/index.ts
   No duplicate formulas in components

â–ˇ Architecture Compliance
   modules/<domain>/ layout â€” no new flat routes/services
   FinancialPostingService for GL writes
   PostgreSQL only â€” no SQLite
   No secrets committed
```

## Architecture v2.1 sub-checklist

- [ ] Repository extends `TenantRepository`
- [ ] No SQL in route handlers
- [ ] No direct GL writes outside `FinancialPostingService`
- [ ] Migration added if schema changed
- [ ] No duplicate business logic
- [ ] No legacy pattern extensions

## Real-Time First sub-checklist

- [ ] Commit before emit
- [ ] Payload includes tenantId, type, id, action, ts
- [ ] version in data when LWW-enabled
- [ ] No cross-tenant leakage
- [ ] Screens update without manual F5
- [ ] No refresh button as primary sync
- [ ] Not polling-only for mutations

## Agent behavior

Before marking any task complete:

1. Walk through applicable checkboxes explicitly in the response
2. If user requests skipping an item, explain compliance risk
3. If feature lacked sync, add emit + subscription + invalidation before claiming done

## Verification commands

```powershell
npm run build:backend
npm run verify:track-f-p4      # if report engines touched
npm run verify:track-e2        # if real-time / modules touched
```

